Higher Education Minister Blade Nzimande briefs the media on measures implemented on COVID-19 within the higher education, science and innovation sectors. * Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. PRETORIA - The Minister of Higher Education, Science and Innovation, Dr Blade Nzimande will brief South Africans on measures to contain the spread of COVID-19 within the sector. READ: Nzimande impressed with COVID-19 readiness at TVET college Nzimande is expected to address other matters including sexual harassment and gender-based violence in universities, business innovation, and recruitment, retention, and progression of black academics. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.